race.comment: LES BRAVES (15) impressed at Geelong before the break and won two jumpouts before a dominant Maiden win here first-up as expected. Three winners have come out of that and fitter he has the talent to take the next step. GELLHORN (11) resumes with a top rider booked and the speedy galloper will use the inside gate. Has raced well at Stakes level and two back was a comfortable metro Maiden winner. Has placed 2/2 fresh and rates a threat. JUGIONG (3) was tracking well before being outgraded at Flemington last time. Needs a good ride but has each-way claims. MACEDONIAN MARVEL (5) resumed here with a narrow defeat and is proven second-up. He won't have to improve much to feature.
